<BlogPost
  title="Protecta 2-Stroke Mix"
  description=""
  category="Motorcycle Equipment"
  categorySlug="motorcycle-equipment"
>
<p>Having trouble with fouled plugs, spooge drippy pipe along with an engine that bogs loads up needing to be throttled up every time you lug it? Then Protecta 2-stroke oil is for you. I have a snowmobile engine builder riding buddy who is also a master tuner of 2-stroke engines &#8211; he really explained things. Premix oil has a flashpoint in it&#8217;s makeup which dictates the temperature it ignites and burns. The lower the flashpoint the sooner the oil ignites. Converting the track oriented KTM 250sx to a dedicated trail machine took some trial and error. It likes to run at high RPM&#8217;s and didn&#8217;t enjoy being a lugger on the trail. Going one plug hotter and the addition of a low flashpoint oil like Protecta oil solved the problem.</p>
<p>Mack</p>
